a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530778\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530778\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104owv1665702836486.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/owv1665702836486.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/owv1665702836486.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"owv1665702836486\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Print Mode\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the data to print.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"owv1665702836486__li_d4508e1_d4509e1_d4510e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">All</span>—prints the complete form\ncomponent, including all data currently in the component, all occurrences in\nthe hitlist, and all fixed text. <p class=\"p\" id=\"owv1665702836486__p_d9848e1_d9849e1_d9850e1\">If header and trailer frames have been\ndefined, they are printed on the top and bottom of each printed page,\nrespectively. If an entity frame does not show all occurrences, or\na field frame does not show all the data it contains, the frame is expanded to\nshow all the data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"owv1665702836486__p_d9851e1_d9852e1_d9853e1\">If all occurrences in the hitlist have not yet been fetched, read triggers are activates to fetch the data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"owv1665702836486__p_d9854e1_d9855e1_d9856e1\">Width definitions in the layout definition of a field are ignored.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"owv1665702836486__li_d4511e1_d4512e1_d4513e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Screen</span>—prints only the data\nthat can be seen on the screen. Applicable only for character based user interface (CHUI). For GUI, it behaves the same as <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component</span>.<p class=\"p\" id=\"owv1665702836486__p_d9857e1_d9858e1_d9859e1\">Any data not visible in the component window is not printed. The dimensions of the component window\nare the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Width</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Depth</span> component properties.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"owv1665702836486__li_d4514e1_d4515e1_d4516e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component</span>—prints the data and\nfixed text on the entire form component. <p class=\"p\" id=\"owv1665702836486__p_d9860e1_d9861e1_d9862e1\">If the form component is larger than\nthe form component window, the part of the form not currently visible is also\nprinted. If the form component is larger than one page, any header\nor trailer which has been defined is printed once, in the same place as it is\npainted on the form component. Uniface does not expand field or entity frames.\nThey are printed as is.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"owv1665702836486__li_d4517e1_d4518e1_d4519e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Clear</span>—similar to All, but clears data\nfrom memory immediately after it has been printed. The hitlist is also dropped.\nThis causes \n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$hits</span> to decrease step by step as the print process progresses. This\nmode is recommended when printing large quantities of data (in batch mode or report component) because it improves performance.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530778\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530778\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Print Mode Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Print Mode Specify the data to print. All —prints the complete form component, including all data currently in the component, all occurrences in the hitlist, and all fixed text. If header and trailer frames have been defined, they are printed on the top and bottom of each printed page, respectively. If an entity frame does not show all occurrences, or a field frame does not show all the data it contains, the frame is expanded to show all the data. If all occurrences in the hitlist have not yet been fetched, read triggers are activates to fetch the data. Width definitions in the layout definition of a field are ignored. Screen —prints only the data that can be seen on the screen. Applicable only for character based user interface (CHUI). For GUI, it behaves the same as Component . Any data not visible in the component window is not printed. The dimensions of the component window are the Width and Depth component properties. Component —prints the data and fixed text on the entire form component. If the form component is larger than the form component window, the part of the form not currently visible is also printed. If the form component is larger than one page, any header or trailer which has been defined is printed once, in the same place as it is painted on the form component. Uniface does not expand field or entity frames. They are printed as is. Clear —similar to All, but clears data from memory immediately after it has been printed. The hitlist is also dropped. This causes $hits to decrease step by step as the print process progresses. This mode is recommended when printing large quantities of data (in batch mode or report component) because it improves performance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}